    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The example last in [this](http://flask.pocoo.org/docs/signals/#subscribing-to-signals) section is pointless because the `recorded` list is never yielded and it is not reachable from anywhere. `connected_to` yields `None`.\n\n```\ndef captured_templates(app):\n    recorded = []\n    def record(template, context):\n        recorded.append((template, context))\n    return template_rendered.connected_to(record, app)\n```\n\nIt's still a meaningful pattern for like what Flask-Testing does, appending to `self.templates` which in deed is reachable from tests. What would be a sensible rewrite?\n",
